---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Game of Tell"
  description="Game of Tell: a two-player deception study using synchronized face video and physiological signals."
>

  <div class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="tag">2021 – present</span>
      <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full bg-[#8b949e]/10 text-[#8b949e] border border-[#30363d]">IRB Approved</span>
      <span class="tag">PsychoPy</span><span class="tag">rPPG</span><span class="tag">OpenFace</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold gradient-text mb-3">Game of Tell</h1>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      A two-player card game designed to study deception, combining face video, remote
      photoplethysmography, and behavioral event logging to model lying and lie detection.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="card mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-3">Motivation</h2>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] leading-relaxed mb-3">
      Inspired by Pinti et al. (2021), who used fNIRS to show that anterior prefrontal cortex
      activity couples between players during a card-game deception task. This study replaces
      brain imaging with face video and remote PPG — signals capturable anywhere with a webcam.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] leading-relaxed">
      Data collection ran from 2021 to 2023 (42+ subjects across pilot and regular sessions).
      Analysis direction is currently being defined: the core questions center on behavioral and
      physiological changes on Lie vs. Truth trials, and whether inter-player synchrony patterns
      predict detection outcomes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- The Game -->
  <section class="card mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-3">The Paradigm</h2>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
      A PsychoPy card game with two roles that alternate each block:
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-4">
      <div class="bg-[#0d1117] rounded-lg p-4 border border-[#30363d]">
        <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-2 text-sm">Informer</h3>
        <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-xs leading-relaxed">Picks a face-down card, then claims it is "Higher" or "Lower" than the Guesser's card — truthfully or as a lie. Wins by successfully deceiving the Guesser.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#0d1117] rounded-lg p-4 border border-[#30363d]">
        <h3 class="font-medium text-white mb-2 text-sm">Guesser</h3>
        <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-xs leading-relaxed">Adjusts a wager (w+/w-), commits ("finish wager"), then guesses "Truth" or "Lie." Wager magnitude determines points won or lost on a correct/incorrect detection.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-sm leading-relaxed">
      Structure: multiple blocks of 6 trials each. 7 trial outcome types: TT, TF, FT, FF (Truth/False × detected/missed) plus instructed conditions (I-T, I-LT, I-LF). Roles swap every block.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Data Collected -->
  <section class="card mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-4">Data Per Session</h2>
    <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
      {[
        ['Face video', 'MP4 recording per player, synchronized to game events'],
        ['rPPG / PhysioCam', 'IBI, RSA magnitude, heart rate, raw RGB channels (b, g, r) at ~30fps'],
        ['OpenFace output', 'Facial AUs (intensity + presence), head pose (pitch/yaw/roll), gaze direction, 2D/3D landmarks'],
        ['PsychoPy event log (stamped)', 'Every button press and game event with game-clock timestamp (seconds)'],
        ['PsychoPy trial log (unstamped)', 'Outcome per trial: cards, claim, truth/lie, winner, running scores'],
        ['Timekeeping CSV', 'Clock alignment anchors — physio instance start times + game start time (Unix epoch)'],
        ['Session metadata', 'JSON: experiment ID, player names, Unix timestamps, dilemma type, final scores'],
      ].map(([k, v]) => (
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-sky-400 shrink-0 w-44">{k}</span>
          <span class="text-[#8b949e]">{v}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Analysis -->
  <section class="card mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-3">Analysis Goals</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[#8b949e]">
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-sky-400 shrink-0">•</span> AU and physiological changes on Lie vs. Truth trials (epoch-locked to trial events)</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-sky-400 shrink-0">•</span> Inter-player physiological synchrony using cross-correlation and Hilbert phase analysis</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-sky-400 shrink-0">•</span> Whether gaze, head pose, or AU features predict whether the Guesser will detect the lie</li>
      <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-sky-400 shrink-0">•</span> Connection to NIH R21 facial micro-movement aims: validating FMM pipeline on naturalistic face video</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card mb-6">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-3">Dataset</h2>
    <p class="text-[#8b949e] text-sm leading-relaxed">
      3 pilot dyads (December 2021) + 5 regular dyads (March–April 2022) + Subject 42 (February 2023).
      All sessions IRB-approved. Data organized by subject with standardized file structure from Sub042 onward.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-sky-400 mb-3">Tech Stack</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      {['PsychoPy', 'Python', 'OpenFace', 'PhysioCam', 'rPPG', 'pandas', 'NumPy',
        'cross-correlation', 'Hilbert transform'].map(t => (
        <span class="tag">{t}</span>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>
